<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Key changes made:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">Removed <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">SUMMARY_FILE</span> constant and all references to it</li>
<li class="break-words">Added <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">SKIP_FILE="overview.txt"</span> constant</li>
<li class="break-words">Added a check to skip "overview.txt" in the <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">process_files</span> function</li>
<li class="break-words">Removed the <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">ollama</span> summarization step, keeping only progress logging</li>
<li class="break-words">Updated log messages to reflect the changes</li>
<li class="break-words">Kept the file splitting functionality but removed the summary generation</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The script now:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">Skips processing any file named "overview.txt"</li>
<li class="break-words">Only logs progress to "progress.log"</li>
<li class="break-words">Still splits files into 100-line chunks but doesn't generate summaries</li>
<li class="break-words">Maintains the same directory traversal and error handling</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">To use:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">chmod +x script.sh</span></li>
<li class="break-words"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">./script.sh</span></li>
<li class="break-words">Check "progress.log" for processing details</li>
</ol>
