<h3 dir="auto" class="">Current Terminal Output</h3>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong>From <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">process_files</span> function</strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">echo "Processing directory: $dir" | tee -a "$MAIN_DIR/$PROGRESS_FILE"</span> - This line outputs "Processing directory: [directory_path]" to both the terminal and the progress log.</li>
<li class="break-words"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">echo "Processing $file_name" | tee -a "$MAIN_DIR/$PROGRESS_FILE"</span> - This line outputs "Processing [filename]" to both the terminal and the progress log.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>No other direct terminal output</strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">All other <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">echo</span> statements redirect to <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">$PROGRESS_FILE</span> or <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">$SUMMARY_FILE</span> using <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">&gt;&gt;</span>, so they don't appear in the terminal.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h3 dir="auto" class="">Expected Behavior</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">You see "Processing directory: ..." and "Processing [filename]" in the terminal as the script runs.</li>
<li class="break-words">All other progress messages (e.g., temp directory creation, chunk processing) and summaries go to the log files only.</li>
</ul>
